# TTS Audio Generation

## Quick Start

Generate audio for a lesson:
```bash
npm run tts:generate -- --lesson 04 --model gemini
```

## Model Strategy: Flash for Words, Pro for Sentences

Two Gemini TTS models are used depending on content type:

### gemini-2.5-flash-tts (single words / short phrases)
- **Use for:** Vocabulary (`words/`), grammar table rows (`grammar/`), grammar table notes
- **Prompt:** `"make sure the word is clearly in Bulgarian with the right pronunciation"`
- **Why:** Better pronunciation accuracy for isolated words

### gemini-2.5-pro-tts (connected text)
- **Use for:** Dialogues, reading texts, listening, grammar examples (full sentences), personal choice models
- **Prompt:** `"Read aloud in a warm, welcoming tone."`
- **Why:** More natural intonation and flow for sentences and paragraphs

### Override: `GRAMMAR_TABLE_PRO_ROWS`
Some grammar table rows need Pro instead of Flash (e.g. multi-syllable numbers like "—Ö–∏–ª—è–¥–∞"). Add the row key to this `Set` in `generate-tts.ts`.

### Common settings
- **API:** Google Cloud TTS via OAuth (`texttospeech.googleapis.com/v1/text:synthesize`)
- **Auth:** Service account (`service-account.json` in project root, gitignored)
- **Output:** MP3
- **Rate limit:** ~10 req/min ‚Üí script uses 6.5s delay between requests
- **Voices:**
  - `Achernar` ‚Äî female (default)
  - `Despina` ‚Äî second female (when two women alternate in dialogues)
  - `Charon` ‚Äî male
  - `Achird` ‚Äî second male (when two men alternate in dialogues)

### Why Gemini over Chirp3-HD

Chirp3-HD (`bg-BG-Chirp3-HD-*`) has accent/stress issues on Bulgarian words. Gemini TTS produces more natural pronunciation with correct stress patterns.

## Fallback Model: Chirp3-HD

```bash
npm run tts:generate -- --lesson 05 --model chirp
```
- Uses API key (`GOOGLE_TTS_API_KEY` in `.env.local`)
- Voices: `bg-BG-Chirp3-HD-Achernar`, `bg-BG-Chirp3-HD-Charon`
- Speaking rate: 0.85
- Rate limit: 10 req/s

## File Structure

```
public/assets/lesson-XX/audio/tts/
  words/         ‚Äî {vocabularyItemId}.mp3
  dialogues/     ‚Äî {exerciseId}-{sectionId}-line-{index}.mp3
  grammar/       ‚Äî {exerciseId}-row-{index}.mp3  (tables)
                   {exerciseId}-card-{index}.mp3  (examples)
                   {exerciseId}-note-{index}.mp3  (table notes)
  texts/         ‚Äî {exerciseId}-p-{index}.mp3     (per paragraph)
                   {exerciseId}-full.mp3           (full text, <2000 chars)
                   {exerciseId}-model.mp3          (personal_choice model)
  listening/     ‚Äî {exerciseId}.mp3
```

## What Gets Generated

| Category | Source | Voice | Model |
|---|---|---|---|
| Vocabulary | `content.vocabulary[].bulgarian` | Female | Flash |
| Illustrated cards | `exercises[type=illustrated_cards].cards[]` (label + sublabels) | Female | Flash |
| Dialogues | `exercises[type=dialogues].sections[].lines[]` | Per speaker | Pro |
| Grammar tables | `exercises[type=grammar_table].rows[]` | Female | Flash (or Pro via override) |
| Grammar table notes | `exercises[type=grammar_table].notes[]` | Female | Flash |
| Grammar visual (pronouns) | `exercises[type=grammar_visual].pronouns[]` | Female | Flash (`{exerciseId}-pronoun-{i}.mp3`) |
| Grammar examples | `exercises[type=grammar_examples].examples[]` | Female | Pro |
| Reading texts | `exercises[type=reading_text].paragraphs[]` | Female/male | Pro |
| Listening | `exercises[].listeningText` | Female | Pro |
| Personal choice models | `exercises[type=personal_choice].model` | Female | Pro |

## What Does NOT Get Generated

- Interactive exercises (fill_blank, dropdown, drag, etc.)
- Cards with `disableTts: true`
- Exercises in per-lesson exclude lists (e.g., workbook exercises)

## Speaker Voice Map (Dialogues)

| Speaker | Voice |
|---|---|
| –ö–ª–∏–µ–Ω—Ç | Female (Achernar) |
| –ü—Ä–æ–¥–∞–≤–∞—á | Male (Charon) |
| Fallback | Alternating by line index (even=female, odd=male) |

### Explicit `voiceGender` on dialogue lines (recommended)

In `exercises.ts`, each dialogue line may set `voiceGender: 'male' | 'female'` (TTS only; not shown in the UI). When set, it overrides the fallback alternation so a **male** line always uses a male voice.

**Two men in a row:** the script alternates **`Charon`** and **`Achird`** (Gemini TTS). Chirp mode has only one Bulgarian male preset, so both map to Chirp Charon.

**Two women in a row:** the script alternates **`Achernar`** and **`Despina`** (Gemini TTS).

When adding new lessons with different speakers, update `SPEAKER_VOICE_MAP` in [generate-tts.ts](mdc:scripts/generate-tts.ts) and/or add `voiceGender` on lines where roles are clear.

## Text Cleaning

Two cleaning functions exist:
- **`cleanForGeminiTTS()`** (Gemini): Light touch ‚Äî strips leading dashes, removes parenthetical labels
- **`cleanForTTS()`** (Chirp): Aggressive ‚Äî converts slashes/dashes to commas, removes exclamation marks, strips parentheses

## Content Rules for TTS Quality

These rules in **content files** directly affect audio quality:
- **Numbers as words** in `listeningText` and `reading_text.paragraphs` ‚Äî write ‚Äû—Å–µ–¥–µ–º–¥–µ—Å–µ—Ç –∏ —à–µ—Å—Ç" not ‚Äû76". TTS reads digits unnaturally.
- **Period, not dash** between sums ‚Äî `'–Ý–µ—Å—Ç–æ—Ç–æ. –ß–µ—Ç–∏—Ä–∏ –µ–≤—Ä–æ.'` not `'–Ý–µ—Å—Ç–æ—Ç–æ ‚Äî —á–µ—Ç–∏—Ä–∏ –µ–≤—Ä–æ.'`. Dashes confuse pacing.
- **No markdown** in text fields ‚Äî TTS reads asterisks, brackets etc. Keep text clean.
- **voiceGender on every dialogue line** where the speaker's gender is clear (male/female). Fallback alternation works but explicit is better.
- **Problematic words** ‚Äî add to `GRAMMAR_TABLE_PRO_ROWS` if a Flash-generated word sounds wrong. Examples: ‚Äû—Ö–∏–ª—è–¥–∞", ‚Äû–º–∏–ª–∏–∞—Ä–¥", ‚Äû–≤–∏–µ —Ä–∞–±–æ—Ç–∏—Ç–µ".

## Audio Files in Git

MP3 files are stored as **regular binary files** in Git (NOT LFS). Vercel does not fetch LFS objects during build, so LFS caused all audio to be deployed as broken pointer files. Total audio is ~28 MB ‚Äî acceptable for Git.

> Never manually move or rename audio files outside of the TTS script ‚Äî paths are convention-based.  
> WAV and OGG files remain in LFS (`.gitattributes`).

## Adding a New Lesson ‚Äî Checklist

1. Ensure `content.ts` and `exercises.ts` are complete for the lesson
2. Check for special cases: `voiceGender: 'male'` on exercises, `disableTts: true` on cards
3. Add any lesson-specific excludes to `READING_TEXT_EXCLUDE` or `SKIP_FULL_TEXT` in generate-tts.ts
4. If dialogues have new speaker roles, add them to `SPEAKER_VOICE_MAP`
5. Run: `npm run tts:generate -- --lesson XX --model gemini`
6. Script skips existing files ‚Äî safe to re-run after fixing issues
7. To regenerate specific files, delete them first, then re-run
8. Verify in browser: `npm run dev` ‚Üí navigate to lesson
9. Commit and push: `git add -A` ‚Üí `git commit` ‚Üí `git push` (LFS handles MP3s automatically)

## Convention-Based Audio Paths

Components use `getTtsAudioPath()` from [src/lib/tts.ts](mdc:src/lib/tts.ts) to construct paths by convention:
```
/assets/lesson-{num}/audio/tts/{category}/{filename}.mp3
```
No manual `audioUrl` needed for vocabulary, dialogues, or grammar ‚Äî the path is derived from exercise ID. Reading texts use `audioUrl` in exercises.ts pointing to the `-full.mp3` file.

